### XI.

Here they took Enoch up on to the fourth heaven where is the course of
sun and moon.

THOSE men took me, and led me up on to the fourth heaven, and showed me
all the successive goings, and all the rays of the light of sun and
moon.

2 And I measured their goings and compared their light, and saw that the
sun's light is greater than the moon's.

3 Its circle and the wheels on which it goes always, like a wind going
past with very marvellous

<span id="page_85">p. 85</span>

speed, and day and night it has no rest. <span
id="fr_1"></span>[1](#fn_1.md)

4 Its passage and return *are accompanied by* four great stars, and each
star has under it a thousand stars, to the right of the sun's wheel,
*and by* four to the left, each having under it a thousand stars,
altogether eight thousand, issuing with the sun continually.

5 And by day fifteen myriads of angels attend it, and by night a
thousand.

6 And six-winged ones issue with the angels before the sun's wheel into
the fiery flames, and a hundred angels kindle the sun and set it alight.

